<p>I have two entities called class and students. There is many to one mapping from student to class. </p>  <pre><code>&lt;many-to-one name="Class" class="Class"&gt;       &lt;column name="ClassID" /&gt;     &lt;/many-to-one&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Below is the mapping in Class.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;bag name="Students" cascade="all-delete-orphan" inverse="true" lazy="extra" batch-size="100"&gt;       &lt;key column="ClassID" foreign-key="ID" /&gt;       &lt;one-to-many class="Student"/&gt;     &lt;/bag&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I need to update UpdatedDateTime column on specific student entity which I have updated. But it is updating all the parent entities and other child entities.</p>  <p>I am using below code to identify the dirty entity on event listener.</p>  <pre><code>public override bool OnFlushDirty(object entity, object id, object[] currentState, object[] previousState,             string[] propertyNames, global::NHibernate.Type.IType[] types)         {             if (entity.GetType().GetInterfaces().Contains(typeof (IAuditEntity))))             {                 int UpdatedDate = Array.IndexOf(propertyNames, "UpdatedDate");                  currentState[UpdatedDate] = DateTime.Now;                  return true;             }             return false;         } </code></pre>  <p>Any help would be appreciated!!</p>